<item>
  <title>Fenced echo</title>
  <dc:creator>Mine Çetinkaya-Rundel</dc:creator>
  <link>https://mine-cetinkaya-rundel.github.io/quarto-tip-a-day/posts/02-fenced-echo/index.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 




<section id="echo-fenced" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="echo-fenced"><code>echo: fenced</code></h2>
<p>If you, like me, spend most of your time writing teaching materials or documentation, I’m sure you’ll find the chunk option <code>echo: fenced</code> just as useful as I do! When you set this option for a code chunk, the chunk is displayed with the fences around it – without a screenshot or using a special verbatim engine.</p>
<p>To get code chunks printed out as</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb1" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode markdown code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb1-1"><span class="in" style="color: #5E5E5E;">```{r}</span></span>
<span id="cb1-2"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;">#| label: simple-arithmetic</span></span>
<span id="cb1-3"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;">#| results: hide</span></span>
<span id="cb1-4"></span>
<span id="cb1-5"><span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">1</span> <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">+</span> <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">1</span></span>
<span id="cb1-6"><span class="in" style="color: #5E5E5E;">```</span></span></code></pre></div>
</div>
<p>add the <code>echo: fenced</code> option to your chunk:</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb2" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode markdown code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode markdown"><span id="cb2-1"><span class="in" style="color: #5E5E5E;">```{r}</span></span>
<span id="cb2-2"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;">#| echo: fenced</span></span>
<span id="cb2-3"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;">#| label: simple-arithmetic</span></span>
<span id="cb2-4"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;">#| results: hide</span></span>
<span id="cb2-5"></span>
<span id="cb2-6"><span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">1</span> <span class="sc" style="color: #5E5E5E;">+</span> <span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;">1</span></span>
<span id="cb2-7"><span class="in" style="color: #5E5E5E;">```</span></span></code></pre></div>
<p>Note that in the output all chunk options other than <code>echo: fenced</code> are shown, so this is a great tool for teaching chunk options as well.</p>
</section>
<section id="learn-more" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="learn-more">Learn more</h2>
<p><a href="https://quarto.org/docs/computations/execution-options.html#fenced-echo">Fenced echo execution option</a></p>


</section>

